+-----------+  compiled/interpreted   +-------------+
| sass/scss | ----------------------> | vanilla CSS |
+-----------+                         +-------------+

* No NEW css feature are added by them
+ Aims to make css futureproof
+ Mixins       Custom Functions
+ Nesting      less code
+ Extension    inherit same property as other element
+ Operators    use math in css

# Is a preprocessor worth learning in 2020?

> To try Sass, you just need to know how to set up the compiler.

- Vanilla CSS is catching up with SASS's functionality?
- Can use Math and pre-built functions with SCSS

## How to organize your CSS?

1. Root Styles
2. Styling Elements / Classes
3. Custom Elements / Classes Conventions
  1. BEM Block-Element-Modifier Model
  2. Object Oriented CSS
  3. Atomic CSS
4. CSS Modules
5. CSS-in-JS

